activities.message:
@low-keytech, Is it possible you could provide a clear explanation describing how this can be exploited **against third-parties?**

Thanks again for your report, and hope to hear back from you soon.

Cheers,
@still

Looks like this is may be a Pakistan carrier that is probably using the Urdu language character set, which doesn't seem to contain an '@' symbol: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GSM_03.38#Urdu_language_.28Arabic_and_basic_Latin_scripts.29

I guess they are trying to do us a "favor" by replacing it with a different character. Please note that this is a low impact issue for a small number of our users, but we've registered the domain at this time. We'd like to review if there are any other better alternatives for messaging to avoid this.

@lowkey-tech do you normally see any other characters being removed/replaced?
